<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4004]  Remove required RDBNAM from ACCSEC. Use SECCHK RDBNAM if none is provided on ACCSEC</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4004</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently Derby requires RDBNAM on ACCSEC. The DDM spec lists it as optional. For &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-728&quot; title=&quot;Unable to create databases whose name containg Chinese characters through the client driver&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-728&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-728&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, in order to negotiate the encoding, EXCSAT and ACCSEC will need to remain EBCDIC, so we want the RDBNAM to be optional.  We can use the RDBNAM sent in SECCHK instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once this is done. Client can be changed to only send RDBNAM on ACCSEC if an EBCDIC conversion is possible.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
